{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-03-12T15:13:15.057Z","role":"user","content":"You are addressing review comments on PR #43 (branch: forge/Hytte-avr) for bead Hytte-avr.\n\n## Review Comments to Address\n\n### Comment 1 (by @copilot-pull-request-reviewer)\n**File**: web/package.json line 41\n\nThe new Vite 8 upgrade still leaves a peer-range mismatch with @tailwindcss/vite: the installed @tailwindcss/vite@4.2.1 declares a peer dependency on Vite \"^5.2.0 || ^6 || ^7\" (see web/package-lock.json). The added npm \"overrides\" entry pins the Vite version used for resolution, but it does not change @tailwindcss/vite’s peer range; depending on npm settings/versions this can still produce peer warnings or ERESOLVE install failures. Consider upgrading `@tailwindcss/vite` to a release that explicitly supports Vite 8, or adjust the dependency strategy so installs don’t rely on bypassing an incompatible peer constraint.\n```suggestion\n    \"vite\": \"^7.0.0\"\n```\n\n### Comment 2 (by @copilot-pull-request-reviewer)\n**File**: web/package.json line 36\n\nVite 8 requires Node \"^20.19.0 || >=22.12.0\" (per the vite package’s engines field in web/package-lock.json). web/package.json doesn’t declare a Node engine, so developers on older Node 20/22 minors may hit confusing install/build errors. Consider adding an \"engines.node\" constraint (and optionally aligning it with CI’s Node 22) to make the requirement explicit and fail fast.\n\n### Comment 3 (by @copilot-pull-request-reviewer)\n**File**: CLAUDE.md line 63\n\nCLAUDE.md is updated to say “Vite 8”, but other repo docs still reference “Vite 7” (e.g. .github/copilot-instructions.md and custom-instructions/repo/.github/copilot-instructions.md). This creates inconsistent guidance about the current frontend toolchain; consider updating those references as part of the same dependency bump.\n```suggestion\n- **Frontend**: React 19, TypeScript 5.9, Vite 7, Tailwind CSS v4, Lucide React icons\n```\n\n### Comment 4 (by @copilot-pull-request-reviewer)\n\n## Pull request overview\n\nUpgrades the frontend build toolchain in `web/` to Vite 8 (Rolldown-based) and records the change in project documentation/changelog.\n\n**Changes:**\n- Bump `vite` to `^8.0.0` and `@vitejs/plugin-react` to `^5.2.0`.\n- Add an npm `overrides` entry intended to address a `@tailwindcss/vite` peer dependency conflict.\n- Update documentation/changelog to reflect the Vite 8 upgrade.\n\n### Reviewed changes\n\nCopilot reviewed 3 out of 4 changed files in this pull request and generated 3 comments.\n\n| File | Description |\n| ---- | ----------- |\n| web/package.json | Updates Vite + React plugin versions; adds overrides for Tailwind’s Vite integration. |\n| web/package-lock.json | Lockfile updates reflecting Vite 8’s dependency graph (Rolldown/lightningcss, etc.). |\n| changelog.d/Hytte-avr.md | Adds a changelog entry for the Vite 8 upgrade. |\n| CLAUDE.md | Updates tech stack docs from Vite 7 → Vite 8. |\n\n<details>\n<summary>Files not reviewed (1)</summary>\n\n* **web/package-lock.json**: Language not supported\n</details>\n\n\n\n\n---\n\nYou can also share your feedback on Copilot code review. [Take the survey](https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/XP6L3XJ).\n\n## Instructions\n\n1. Address ALL review comments above\n2. Make the requested changes — follow the reviewer's guidance\n3. Ensure the project still builds and tests pass after changes\n4. Commit with message: \"fix: address review comments for Hytte-avr\"\n5. Push to branch: forge/Hytte-avr\n\n## Working Directory\n\nC:\\source\\fhigit\\Hytte\\.workers\\Hytte-avr\n"}
